\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} Statements for Anti\PYGZhy{}Scientism Argument}

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} Statement 1: Direct Challenge}
\PYG{l+s+sb}{```}
\PYG{l+s+sb}{The reductive impulses of the ``science of math\PYGZsq{}\PYGZsq{} movement tacitly assume mathematics education can be reduced to a finite, closed system of instructional procedures. G√∂del\PYGZsq{}s theorem, applied to the HC, proves this assumption is false. Elementary arithmetic is inherently open.}
