\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} Statement 2: Vessels vs. Agents}
\PYG{l+s+sb}{```}
\PYG{l+s+sb}{We are not finite vessels to be filled with mathematical knowledge and emptied onto standardized tests. The mathematics we invent‚Äîeven at the elementary level‚Äînecessarily transcends any finite characterization of it. Students are not deficient recipients of predetermined procedures; they are agents whose mathematical understanding inherently exceeds any static formalization.}
